<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued April 22 at 10:28PM MDT until April 22 at 10:45PM MDT by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1045 PM MDT
FOR EASTERN KIOWA COUNTY...
At 1028 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 8 miles north of Towner to 10 miles north of Hartman,
moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Towner.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
